;; nbb classpath for the cljs-only async READ surface (gmail.async-*) and its
;; tests. nbb resolves gmail.async-client / gmail.async-threads /
;; gmail.async-history from `src`, their tests from `test`, and the reused
;; gmail.client/api-base (a plain portable def in a .cljc; nbb reads the .cljc
;; and the #?(:clj ...) forms simply drop out under cljs) also from `src`, when
;; running e.g. `npx nbb test/gmail/async_client_test.cljs`.
;; The JVM/.cljc namespaces (client transport, threads, labels, drafts,
;; history, mime, attachments, retry, watch) are NOT on the nbb side -- they
;; stay `clojure -M:test`.
{:paths ["src" "test"]}
